The function first checks if the input is 0, in which case it returns false.

If the input is not 0, we take the natural logarithm base 10 of the input. This gives us the exponent of 3 that would give us the input.

We check if the exponent is an integer, and if the exponent multiplied by 3 gives us the input. If it does, we return true.

Otherwise, we return false.

